description.narrative: The objective of the Education Quality and Secondary Education Project is to improve access to a quality lower secondary education for low income students, especially in indigenous communities, through improved primary education completion rates for overage students, strengthened flexible lower secondary education modalities and school management. The main changes to the project and rationale are: 1) revisions to the scope of some activities, due to changing government priorities amid fiscal constraints and an increase in demand for lower secondary school scholarships, resulting in greater project emphasis on facilitators for telesecundarias and for the scholarship program; 2) changes to targets of some intermediate result indicators consistent with the changes to project activities, and revisions to the wording and targets of some intermediate result indicators to enhance clarity; and 3) a reallocation of grant proceeds consistent with the changes to project activities.
